# Frontend

- Next.js App Router — Server Components first.
- Client Components only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs).
- TanStack Query for all server state and API calls.
- Zustand only for client UI state (sidebar, view toggles) — not server data.
- No prop drilling — use composition or stores for shared UI state.
- Lazy load heavy components and routes.
- Route groups for auth, dashboard, onboarding layouts.
- Suspense boundaries around async server components where applicable.
